              "text": "Havana was founded in 1519 by the Spanish, and its historic center has been a UNESCO World Heritage Site since 1982. Start at Plaza de la Catedral: the San Cristóbal Cathedral, completed in 1777 by the Jesuits, features an asymmetrical baroque facade - its two towers aren't the same width, a rare occurrence in colonial architecture. The square is framed by the Palacio del Marqués de Aguas Claras and the Palacio del Conde de Lombillo, both from the 18th century.",
