              "text": "El Capitolio, constructed from 1926 to 1929 by architect Eugenio Rayneri Piedra, measures 207 meters long. Its dome rises to 92 meters - the world's third-highest at the time. Inside, the bronze Statue of the Republic (14.6 m, 30 tons) was then the world's third-largest covered statue. Beneath the dome, a 25-carat diamond set in the floor marks kilometer zero for all Cuban roads. The Paseo del Prado, laid out in 1772 and redesigned in 1928 by French urban planner Forestier, connects the Capitol to the Malecón.",
